'''[[全球暖化|全球暖化]]否定說'''（{{lang-en|global warming denial}}）或'''氣候变化否定论'''（{{lang-en|climate change denial}}）是指相關團體活動、個人行為，否定科學界[[关于气候变化的科学观点|公認存在的氣候变化現象]]。持此說的人士、集團或組織，大致包含有以下行為：[[全球变暖的效应|否認人為導致氣候变化的現象]]、{{tsl|en|Attribution of recent climate change|近期气候变化的诱因|否認全球暖化乃因人類行所產生}}、默認有氣候变化現象的科學證據，但拒絕採取任何抑制全球暖化現象之措拖<ref>{{Cite book |author=National Center for Science Education 2010 |title=The first pillar of climate change denial}}</ref>。有些持氣候变化否定說的人士，把自己定位為'''氣候变化懷疑論者'''<ref name="Matthews 153–168">{{Cite journal|last=Matthews|first=Paul|date=3 April 2015|title=Why Are People Skeptical about Climate Change? Some Insights from Blog Comments|journal=Environmental Communication|language=en|volume=9|issue=2|pages=153–168|doi=10.1080/17524032.2014.999694|issn=1752-4032}}</ref><ref name="NCSE-why-denial">{{cite web | url=http://ncse.com/climate/denial/why-is-it-called-denial | title=Why Is It Called Denial? | publisher=[[National_Center_for_Science_Education|National Center for Science Education]] | accessdate=21 January 2016 | date=15 January 2016 | archive-date=2016-05-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526180046/http://ncse.com/climate/denial/why-is-it-called-denial | dead-url=no }}</ref>，但這並不符合科學對懷疑論的標準，因此科學界普遍將此類人士仍歸納為'''氣候变化否定者'''<ref>{{Cite book |author=Dunlap 2013 |title=Climate Change Skepticism and Denial: An Introduction |pages=691－698}} There is debate over which term is most appropriate… Those involved in challenging climate science label themselves "skeptics"… Yet skepticism is…a common characteristic of scientists, making it inappropriate to allow those who deny AGW to don the mantle of skeptics…It seems best to think of skepticism-denial as a continuum, with some individuals (and interest groups) holding a skeptical view of AGW…and others in complete denial</ref><ref name="auto">{{Cite journal |title=Climate and environmental science denial: A review of the scientific literature published in 1990-2015 |first=Karin Edvardsson|display-authors=et al |last=Björnberg |journal=[[Journal_of_Cleaner_Production|Journal of Cleaner Production]] |volume=167 |year=2017 |pages= 229–241 |doi=10.1016/j.jclepro.2017.08.066 |url= |ref=harv }}</ref><ref name="O'Neill Boykoff 2010">{{cite journal | last=O'Neill | first=Saffron J. | author2=sjoneill@unimelb.edu.au | last3=Boykoff | first3=Max | title=Climate denier, skeptic, or contrarian? | journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences | volume=107 | issue=39 | date=28 September 2010 | issn=0027-8424| pmid=20807754 | pages=E151 | doi=10.1073/pnas.1010507107 |quote=Using the language of denialism brings a moralistic tone into the climate change debate that we would do well to avoid. Further, labeling views as denialist has the potential to inappropriately link such views with Holocaust denial… However, skepticism forms an integral part of the scientific method and thus the term is frequently misapplied in such phrases as "climate change skeptic".|bibcode = 2010PNAS..107E.151O | pmc=2947866}}</ref>。

目前有強烈的[[科學共識|科學共識]]認為，人類經濟活動造成近幾十年的全球暖化，對於「在近幾十年，人為造成的全球暖化存在，並正在發生」是事實的這點，在學術界當中是沒有爭議的<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tampabay.com/archive/2013/05/20/the-results-are-in-on-global-warming/ |title=THE RESULTS ARE IN ON GLOBAL WARMING |access-date=2020-09-08 |archive-date=2021-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304090935/https://www.tampabay.com/archive/2013/05/20/the-results-are-in-on-global-warming/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。超過97%的氣候科學家認為「全球暖化存在，且人類活動極有可能是導致近半個世紀的全球暖化現象的主要原因」<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://climate.nasa.gov/scientific-consensus/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2018-04-07 |archive-date=2018-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628042920/https://climate.nasa.gov/scientific-consensus/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。近年大眾對地球暖化的重視程度明顯提升<ref>{{Citation | first=Spencer | last=Weart | author-link=Spencer R. Weart | contribution=The Public and Climate Change | contribution-url=http://www.aip.org/history/climate/Public.htm | title=The Discovery of Global Warming | editor-first=Spencer | editor-last=Weart | editor-link=Spencer R. Weart | url=http://www.aip.org/history/climate/index.html | publisher=[[American_Institute_of_Physics|American Institute of Physics]] | year=2006 | accessdate=2007-04-14 | archive-date=2015-06-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150622091631/http://www.aip.org/history/climate/index.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==全球暖化否定活動及成因==
科學界普遍認定，[[全球暖化|全球暖化]]不但是已存在的事實，而且從各種科學根據來看，最主要是由人為活動產生[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]及[[甲烷|甲烷]]的排放、加劇[[溫室效應|溫室效應]]所造成，因此直接規範二氧化碳及甲烷的排放，應可極有效地減少溫室效應、改善全球暖化的現象<ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://environment.nationalgeographic.com/environment/global-warming/gw-causes/|title=What Causes Global Warming?|accessdate=2016-11-04|archive-date=2013-07-24|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6IMS5oHVb?url=http://environment.nationalgeographic.com/environment/global-warming/gw-causes/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://www.ucsusa.org/our-work/global-warming/science-and-impacts/global-warming-science#.WCE_hxJ97R1|title=The science is clear. Global warming is happening. We are the primary cause|accessdate=2016-11-04|archive-date=2016-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030143942/http://www.ucsusa.org/our-work/global-warming/science-and-impacts/global-warming-science#.WCE_hxJ97R1|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|URL=https://www.epa.gov/climate-change-science/causes-climate-change|title=Causes of Climate Change|accessdate=2016-11-04|archive-date=2016-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104203802/https://www.epa.gov/climate-change-science/causes-climate-change|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

但規範二氧化碳及甲烷的排放，會造成特定工業及利益團體的損失，因此由工業界、政治界、特定意識形態之利益團體所鼓吹，保守媒體及批判博克所支持的各種全球暖化否定活動<ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://scienceblogs.com/denialism/about/|title=Hello Scienceblogs|accessdate=2016-11-04|archive-date=2016-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107072636/http://scienceblogs.com/denialism/about/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|URL=http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1748-9326/7/4/044005;jsessionid=FDC8906CB1C239F1DCA3CBAC3BC222B4.c1.iopscience.cld.iop.org|title=Cross-national comparison of the presence of climate scepticism in the print media in six countries, 2007–10}}</ref>，在近幾十年來大規模展開，目的是要讓一般大眾，對科學界公認存在之全球暖化產生懷疑或不確定感，以封殺可扼制全球暖化的諸多政策。這些活動在美國最為活躍，被稱為「否認機器」（{{lang|en|Denial machine}}） <ref>{{Cite web |URL=http://ossfoundation.us/projects/environment/global-warming/myths/the-denial-machine |title=The Denial Machine |accessdate=2016-11-04 |archive-date=2016-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222035142/http://ossfoundation.us/projects/environment/global-warming/myths/the-denial-machine |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

部分活動根據各種不實的證據，利用工業界資助的美國少數科學家和保守派媒體，來否認全球暖化，公開指稱全球暖化是騙局。

有數據統計，超過90%質詢全球暖化現象的論述，都是由右翼智囊團所出，而相關團體或個人因為這些全球暖化否定活動，加起來每年約有9億美金的收入<ref>{{Cite book |author=Jacques, Dunlap & Freeman 2008 |title=The organisation of denial: Conservative think tanks and environmental scepticism |pages=351}} Conservative think tanks…and their backers launched a full-scale counter-movement… We suggest that this counter-movement has been central to the reversal of US support for environmental protection, both domestically and internationally. Its major tactic has been disputing the seriousness of environmental problems and undermining environmental science by promoting what we term 'environmental scepticism </ref><ref>{{Cite book |author=Jordi Xifra |title=Climate Change Deniers and Advocacy: A Situational Theory of Publics Approach |publisher=American Behavioral Scientist| date = 2016 |  pages = Vol. 60, (3), , 276–287 }}</ref>。這些團體為數上百，他們公然無視全球暖化會帶來重大人類及生態災害的科學證據、進行各種為利益團體所金援策動的全球暖化否定活動，常常被拿來與早期那些由煙草工業金援、漠視科學證據、矢口否定煙草對人體有害的否定活動相提並論<ref>{{Cite web |URL= 
